entation with clear, immediately profitable trades. Uncertainty remains high throughout: proposers infer others' valuations indirectly from what they accept or reject, and responders must guess whether a proposer is offering a genuinely mutual-gain trade or attempting to exploit unknown valuations. In this forecasted play-through, trades gradually reveal that duck-green-5428 and alligator-orange-1621 both prize red and purple, while dolphin-pink-1017 is willing to trade purple away cheaply and tries to assemble more red and some blue. Over time, offers become slightly more tailored and conservative as players respond to observed acceptances and rejections, but no one fully learns the others' exact values within the three-round horizon.",
